properties.Name: Cedar East
properties.Description: An apartment run by the University of Washington (Seattle), and also my current residence.

properties.Name: Husky Union Building (HUB)
properties.Description: UW's building that provides entertainment, food, spaces for events and more. The piano located on the second floor is my daily hangout spot with the best of my friends.

properties.Name: QFC - University Village
properties.Description: A QFC branch located in University Village. This is where I purchase ingredients for most of my meals during the weekdays.

properties.Name: Intramural Activities Building (IMA)
properties.Description: UW's facilities catering to various types of sports. This is where I used to badminton almost daily for almost 2 years in a row.

properties.Name: Bluefin Sushi & Seafood Buffet
properties.Description: An expensive buffet that opens on lunch and dinner hours every day of the week. I usually find myself digging into an unspeakable amount of raw Salmon with friends on special occasions.

properties.Name: Chase Bank
properties.Description: A regular Chase Bank that I visit whenever I have to take care of financial concerns.

properties.Name: Dollar Tree
properties.Description: Student's best friend. I end up here near the end of the month, when stress levels are high, and personal funds are low.

properties.Name: Musashi's
properties.Description: A cheap sushi joint that has fewer than 20 seats and accepts cash only. This place is popular among UW students, and is packed on weekends. They are closed on Sundays and Mondays.

properties.Name: Menchie's Frozen Yogurt
properties.Description: On Fridays at 9PM until 11PM, every cup no matter the weight will cost you $5 + tax. Many of my sweet-toothed friends show up here during Friday nights.

properties.Name: Hansee Hall
properties.Description: Another of UW's housing buildings much like the Cedar Apartments. I used to show up here so often I would call it my second home simply because there are so many grand pianos here just waiting to be played.
